Rob, in 3.3, there is now new API in the IDE class for opening an IFileStore directly. You may want to consider using this instead although you do have a dependency on org.eclipse.ui.ide.

IFileStore store = EFS.getLocalFileSystem().getStore(file.toURI());
IDE.openEditorOnFileStore(page, store);

Alternatively, you can use FileStoreEditorInput directly. I guess you guys could consider changing the @deprecated to point people there instead?
